The National Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Prince Uche Secondus, on behalf of the party, on Monday, congratulated former Governor Adams Oshiohmole of Edo State, on his election as the National Chairman of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) at the party’s national convention on Saturday.
Secondus, in a statement on Monday by his Media Aide, Ike Abonyi, Secondus expressed optimism that Oshiomhole’s election as APC national chairman would deepen democracy in Nigeria.
The PDP National Chairman in the statement declared: “On behalf of my party, the main opposition PDP, I wish to congratulate you and pray that democracy would gain a lot in your climbing to the exalted office of your party.
“May I assure you of the PDP’s readiness to provide robust and constructive criticism and hope that the environment would be made conducive for all democratic institutions to strive.”

















